node.text: We closed on our new house today! 🎉I can’t believe it! What a whirlwind the last two months have been! I wanted to give you a full home tour of the empty house before we move in this weekend Stay tuned until the very end...that’s when I share the big project we have planned for the house and one of the main reasons why we decided to move! We can’t wait to move in, get settled, and begin sharing this new adventure with all of you! ❤️🏡

node.text:
Today I’m sharing a walk through of my entire house (every single room!), which I’ve actually never done before on my page! I’m sharing rooms I’ve never shown before including my laundry room and mud room! 

If you missed it, we are selling our house! Get all the info on our move on my website, Mytexashouse.com. All sources are linked on the LIKEtoKNOW.it app or by clicking the link in my IG bio!

*update: House sold. We moved! 

#hometour #realestate #houseforsale #mytexashouse #texashomes #texasrealestate #falldecor #homedecor

node.title: We’re Selling Our House!: A Complete Home Tour of “Mytexashouse”!

node.text: Here’s my super easy way to put on a duvet cover! No more actually climbing inside of the duvet to install it! 🙈😂 The first step, which isn’t shown, is to turn the duvet cover INSIDE OUT! Then lay the duvet insert over the cover and tie all four sides of the duvet to the insert! Roll them like a burrito. Turn back out the ends like a sandwich baggie, and then voila!✨...the duvet cover is perfectly placed on the duvet in under 2 minutes!🙌🏻 And you can do this technique on your bed instead of the floor if you want. 😉 Link to products/outfit: http://liketk.it/2LMSl

node.title: How to put on a duvet cover in under 2 minutes!

node.text: Back finally with another model home tour! This 5 bedroom, 5 bathroom home has over 5300 square feet and includes a large media room, courtyard, and study. The model is called the “Vanguard” and builder is Toll Brothers. This model home as shown here is priced at $1.5 million. I am not a realtor, just love showing you beautiful homes! Check out my website at: Mytexashouse.com

node.title: New Model Home Tour: Mediterranean Style, Frisco, TX, priced at $1.5 Mil

node.text: This is a beautiful home we toured today by Darling Homes in the Montgomery Farms neighborhood in Allen, TX. This is a 4 bedroom home (option for 5th bedroom) with about 5,000 square feet of living space. My favorite part of the home was the large open living room and kitchen space with all the floor to ceiling windows overlooking the patio! I also LOVE that there was a huge pantry and even a prep kitchen! Check out the IGTV video for the full tour of this beautiful home! What is your favorite part of this home?!!

node.title: Model Home Tour: Darling Homes, Allen, TX (priced from: $900K+)

node.text:
This model home is in Arlington, Texas (right near Dallas. TX). This is a Toll Brothers Home in the Viridian master planned community. The model is called the “Valen”. It has 5 bedrooms, and around 4000+ sq feet. The starting price of this home is around $615K, but upgraded as shown in this model would be between $800K to $900K. Website: https://www.tollbrothers.com/luxury-homes-for-sale/Texas/Viridian?amp=true
**I’m not a realtor, just show these model tours for fun!

node.title: Modern Farmhouse Model Home Tour: Arlington, TX, Toll Bros. Homes ($615K+)

node.text:
We’ve had an amazing trip, but I’m missing this little girl so much! Can’t wait to get back to Texas to give her a big hug! 🐶❤️ Tomorrow, Dusty and I are going to spend a little more time here in Charlottesville before driving back to Washington DC so we can fly back to Florida and pick up our kids from their grandparents! Crazy, I know!🤪 We’ve spent A LOT of time in the air this past week! We fly home the next day and I’m so looking forward to sleeping in my own bed with Jessie snuggled up to me!🥰

node.text: We had a wonderful day with family celebrating the wedding of my cousin, Brenna! Such a sweet, beautiful couple and such a gorgeous wedding venue (I shared some views of this special event in my stories)! ❤️ The stunning scenery as well as the architecture of all the buildings here is making me miss living in Virginia! Dusty and I lived in Charlottesville, VA when we first got married….almost 20 years ago! Tomorrow we are heading to Charlottesville to see what the town looks like now and to reminisce about our time there as newlyweds! I’ll share where we first lived when we got married in my stories tomorrow! Have a great night! #wedding #weddingguest #virginiaisforlovers ❤️

node.text:
House hunting in Florida and I think we found the one! Lol! 🏰 😂 Just kidding….no seriously, we aren’t moving, I promise! But we did spend the day today at Magic Kingdom! (Yes, again!😉) We are here for a few days at Disney World before we drop off the kids with their grandparents who live in Orlando, and then Dusty and I are flying up to Virginia for a wedding! Thankfully the weather wasn’t bad today…tomorrow we are expecting rain. But we will make the best of it in while wearing our ponchos…it’s my birthday tomorrow after all! ☔️😁 

P.S. Does it look like the Donald on Dusty’s shirt is trying to fight me in the second pic?!😂 

I linked my outfit on the LTK app! http://liketk.it/3j8WJ #liketkit @liketoknow.it #LTKunder50 #LTKunder100

node.text: Today I’m sharing our 3D pool design video! Head to my stories today to see the entire video which shows in beautiful detail how our backyard will look soon(ish)! 🤗 I’ll also save the entire video in my story highlights! Wan’t wait to see this design take shape in our backyard!! Planning to have a big 4th of July BBQ and swim party here next year! ❤️🤍💙

node.text:
We finally got all of our new drapery installed in our bedroom and I’m so in love with how they turned out! We chose French return style curtain rods and I think they fit my room and French country style perfectly! Swipe to see what the room looks like at night when we go to sleep with the motorized window shades and curtains closed. It was a challenge in here to figure out how to cover all the windows including the small transom windows as well as a wall of windows with a French door! But I think everything worked out just how I hoped! 

Head to my stories for a closer look at the new drapery and rods as well as all the links! These were custom window coverings, but I linked similar curtains and rods, and all my bedroom sources on the LTK app! Bedding, rug, and wall art from the My Texas House collection at Walmart! http://liketk.it/3iRoa
